id: pm-lp4j
title: Hide internal test-runs-worker from default help/contracts and route it under the test execution plumbing
description: "all-status review 2026-07-06/07 found the live top-level help and contracts still expose test-runs-worker as a command even though its description says it is an internal background worker command. This bloats the agent-facing surface and should not count as a canonical noun or user command in pm-n7rr. Duplicate check: searched all statuses for test-runs-worker/internal worker/help surface; only closed general help/coverage items and the broad simplification epic matched, no focused item exists."
type: Task
status: open
priority: 2
tags[4]: agent-ux,"area:cli",internal-command,simplification
created_at: "2026-07-06T22:23:03.453Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-16T05:45:18.983Z"
author: codex
estimated_minutes: 120
acceptance_criteria: test-runs-worker is hidden from default pm --help and from default contracts summaries; an explicit internal/plumbing discovery path remains for the worker when needed by test-run orchestration; no user-facing feature is removed; contracts/completions/docs/tests are updated so the worker cannot reappear as a canonical top-level command.
parent: pm-n7rr
risk: low
confidence: high
